<h1>Typography</h1>
<p>Typography is the art of arranging type to create clear hierarchy, improving readability, reinforcing brand expression, and bringing consistency across product experiences.</p>

{{ heading('Overview', '2') }}
{{ heading('Typography defines hierarchy', '3') }}
<p>Weight, size, and spacing work together, directing the eye from the most critical information to supporting details. Consistent typographic hierarchy makes interfaces easier to scan and understand at a glance.</p>

{{ heading('Typography has purpose', '3') }}
<p>Vivid assigns meaning to type through dedicated scales and styles. Mono is used for code, and every typescale is designed specifically for UI.</p>

{{ heading('Font', '2') }}
<img src="/assets/images/spezia.png" alt="" style="display: inline-block; max-height: 50px;float: right" />
<div style="max-width: 400px;">
	<p>Vivid utilizes the <a href="https://luzi-type.ch/spezia">Spezia font</a>, a sans-serif typeface designed to be as adaptable as possible. Vivid uses the condensed and ultra-condensed variants across our UI.</p>
</div>
<img src="/assets/images/spezia-mono.png" alt="Spezia mono typeface" style="display: block; max-height: 50px; float: right;" />
<div style="max-width: 400px;">
  {{ heading('Mono', '3') }}
  <p><b>Spezia mono</b> is used for code, inline code snippets, keyboard commands, tokens / technical identifiers.</p>
</div>

{{ heading('Typescales', '2') }}
<p>Vivid offers two typescales: heading and body. Together they create clear visual pairings across the UI, with all line heights aligned to the 4px grid.</p>
<p>Both scales are designed for UI usage first — optimised for high-density layouts where clarity and legibility matter most.</p>
